      "message": "I added ADATASPACE_SRGB to gColorSpaceTable when I moved it to SkNDKConversions. It\u0027s not necessary, though, based on the current code. SkImageGeneratorNDK is the only code that calls SkNDKConversions::toColorSpace, and AImageDecoder never reports ADATASPACE_SCRGB. (Even if it did, the generator falls back to SRGB anyway.)\n\ntoDataSpace will always return ADATASPACE_SRGB first, since they\u0027re identical, as far as Skia is concerned.\n\nThat said, including it is more complete, and just results in an extra iteration through the loop. So I lean towards having it there but don\u0027t have a strong preference.",
